==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: faculæ
<hw>fac"u*l⟦ae⟧</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L., pl.
<ets>of facula</ets> a little torch.]</ety> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>
<def>Groups of small shining spots on the surface of the sun which are
brighter than the other parts of the <partof>photosphere</partof>. They
are generally seen in the neighborhood of the dark spots, and are
supposed to be elevated portions of the photosphere.</def>
<rj><au>Newcomb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

